<br>
Because it is a simple trade, I place the money in the window, they place the item in the window.  I check and verify it is indeed what I think I am buying.  hit trade.  If the item is changed you would need to hit trade again because the trade would be canceled so the item could be changed.  <br>
<br>
So how is level a deciding factor in that entire process?<br>
<br>
I dont know you but I think you should re-think how you just brush all under 60 folks aside.  One example of a level 60 guilded player who has questionable ethics has been listed above.  Check the flame forum, etc for many more examples.<br>
<br>
Name your worst scammer I will do a trade with them.  You can only be scammed if you dont take simple steps to prevent it.<br>
