<br>
My rule is one - one trade. You put money in the window, I put the item. I always ask that buyee check it and make sure that they can wear it, and it is what they are looking for. Nothing I hate worse than having to give money back. <br>
<br>
After all is said and done, then I'll grab my wizzie and come down to pick up the cash from my trader. No real big issue. Just cause the trader isn't high level doesn't mean they aren't trustworthy. You just gotta be careful, and think. If it doesn't feel right, don't do it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
